@startuml data-model
title "Where should Cable/Port data live? (tuna-f1sh's 3 options vs. the chosen approach)"
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
hide circle

class SystemProfile {
  buses: Vec<Bus>
  ..chosen..
  +typec_ports: Option<Vec<TypecPort>>
}

class Bus {
  name: String
  host_controller: String
  devices: Option<Vec<Device>>
  --
  path(): Option<PathBuf>  ' computed, not stored
}

class Device {
  location_id: DeviceLocation
  --
  port_path(): PortPath   ' derived from location_id
}

class DeviceLocation {
  bus: u8
  tree_positions: Vec<u8>
  number: u8
  --
  ' shape + FromStr are a direct encoding
  ' of macOS system_profiler's
  ' "LocationReg / DeviceNo" string
}

class PortPath {
  bus: u8
  ports: Vec<u8>
  --
  FromStr / Display <-> Linux sysfs
  device name ("1-1.3.4")
}

class TypecPort {
  name: String
  device_links: Option<Vec<PortPath>>
  partner: Option<Partner>
  cable: Option<Cable>
  ..
}

DeviceLocation .right.> PortPath : "From<DeviceLocation>\nfor PortPath (exists)"
Device --> DeviceLocation : location_id
Device ..> PortPath : port_path()

SystemProfile *-- Bus
Bus o-- Device
SystemProfile "chosen: top-level,\nnot nested in Bus" *-- TypecPort
TypecPort ..> PortPath : device_links\n(correlation key,\nnever required)
PortPath ..> Device : "resolves via\nSystemProfile::get_node()\nonly when Some"

note right of Bus
  **Option "part of Bus"  -- discarded**
  Bus has no *stored* syspath (only a
  computed one from usb_bus_number).
  Kernel source says DT-only/UCSI systems
  (this issue's own hardware) get no ACPI
  companion link at all, so device_links
  is expected to be None there -- inferred
  from port-mapper.c, not yet empirically
  checked against this thread's dumps.
  Either way: no way to know *which* Bus a
  port belongs to without the same
  correlation this is meant to provide.
  Chicken-and-egg.
end note

note right of DeviceLocation
  **Option "extend DeviceLocation" -- discarded**
  Its FromStr parsing (string Deserialize
  path) is a literal encoding of macOS
  system_profiler's location register
  string (see doc comment) -- even though
  the struct itself is already populated
  directly by the Linux backends today.
  Extending it would still grow a type
  whose string contract is macOS-specific.
end note

note right of PortPath
  **Option "extend Path" -- partially taken**
  Path/PortPath itself is left untouched.
  Reused only as the *join key* -- the
  new semantic data (alt-modes, roles,
  PD revision, e-marker) lives on the
  new TypecPort type instead.
end note

note bottom of TypecPort
  **Chosen: top-level Option<Vec<TypecPort>> on SystemProfile**
  This is the shape first proposed in
  comment from 2026-07-11 -- unchanged
  by this design pass, which only answers
  the correlation-mechanism question.
end note

@enduml
